3. Initialize object (run constructor)

Thread contention: multiple threads compete for the same resource (like a lock), so some have to wait.
👉 Example: many requests in a Spring Boot service trying to update the same cache entry, causing delays.

Thread starvation: a thread never gets a chance to run because resources are exhausted.
👉 Example: all threads in a pool are blocked on a slow API call, so new requests never get processed.
🔥 Example: API Gateway protection
- rate limiting
- circuit breaker
- request throttling
